<br>
Depending on weather you wanna ruin your faction, there are plent of places to solo.<br>
<br>
The barb village in west karana<br>
Dorfs in BB<br>
If your really good, specters in ferrot<br>
Kiting in the overthere is great exp also when you get jboots<br>
<br>
Also, one of the best ways to get exp when you start approaching lvl 40 are yeti's in the dreadlands, they have minimal hitpoints, (I think about 1800 hpts), and can be soloed easily when you get to lvl 39. Doing yeti's in a group is nice exp also.<br>
<br>
<br>
Grouping<br>
<br>
group in ogguk can do fairly well<br>
Cazic Thule, the planks, AoF, or any of the pools,<br>
Sol B, King room, left room, bats<br>
Grouping in the overthere with a necro can be awesome exp<br>
<br>
<br>
Just some quick stuff off the top of my head, give me time to think about it and I can post more, although I would encourage you group as much as possible. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
<br>
Drin<br>
 <p><b><font size=</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uheihache.showPublicProfile?language=EN>heihache</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/2/01 7:53:35 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: yeah...</span><hr size=1> At 37 I went to Iceclad and Easte Waste.  There are 2 places that are good.  I;ll explain them both:<br>
<br>
Iceclad:<br>
<br>
Right at the port in spot.  Kill the Snow Dervish.  Loot sucks, but exp is very good.  Many people will contend this, but let me explain.  There is a &quot;safe spot&quot;  right near the portal.  When you port in, your always facing the exit.  Run straight out.  When you come out, you will see a rock to the left, a rock to the right, and a little distance out (about 200-300 feet) there is another boulder sticking up.  It is just a little left of the entrance (if facing out of entrance) right near shore.  Med on the side of this boulder, this is the safe spot.  Nothing wanders near here except one Snow derv that comes by once every 25 minutes (I timed it).  It took me 3 LONG days to find this spot, so use it well <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   No cash is dropped, but sometimes you can get a ring that is +3 int +10 mana, Shoulders that are +10 mana, and a range slot item that is +3 int.  <br>
<br>
Easte Waste<br>
<br>
Ulthorks all the way!!!  The loot is good, xp rocks, and tusks (hint save the tusks, there is a quest for them that can net you 2.5k pp).  Loc to go hunt is roughly pos 800 neg 800.  From the bridge, turn left and head north following shore.  you can't miss the Ulthorks.  Very easy to kite here.  Medding is done on the shore and is relativily safe.  <br>
<br>
I'm 42 now and if I'm in a soloing mood, I do Ulthorks.  Can't do Snow dervs as at 41 most seemed to turn green.  Ulthorks are all blue at 42 and xp is decent considering I only use 30% mana to kill one.  Good hunting.  O, by the way, snow dervs at 38 cost me 45% mana to kill solo, ulthorks required roughly the same. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umaultar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maultar</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_bluespot.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/2/01 8:13:29 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: yeah...</span><hr size=1> Boy the Velious post there is something I may try to relive the monotony of OT.  I went from 34-40 so far in OT soloing mostly blues.  I have no JBOOTS I tip for sows from surrounding druids and tip for clarity.  I tp for big cash and buy 10 charge sow potions for when there are no druids present.  Usually pull one blue, loot, pull another, loot, then med.  Simple and to soem as boring as that.  I clean and do other things while medding.  Do this at the ledge and med on corner rim on the steep slope that is the opening to the valley to FM zone.  I use the DE hide feature it makes mobs look at u indifferently.  but if you up that high mobs usually dont see u.  Unless some bastard trains you.  Looks like we have a few options here.  Gonna see if I can score some of them int items though <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> . <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uleews.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Leews</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice<